From: Johan van der Berg <johan@example.com>
Date: Tue, 18 Mar 2026 10:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm/rocket: Fix NULL pointer dereference in IOMMU domain cleanup

The rocket_job_cleanup() function calls rocket_iommu_domain_put() without
checking if job->domain is NULL. This causes a kernel crash when
rocket_iommu_domain_get() returns NULL during job submission.

Add NULL check in rocket_job_cleanup() to prevent dereferencing a NULL
pointer during cleanup.

Crash trace:
  Unable to handle kernel NULL pointer dereference at virtual address 0000000000000008
  pc : rocket_iommu_domain_put+0x20/0xa8 [rocket]
  lr : rocket_job_cleanup+0x20/0x254 [rocket]
  Call trace:
   rocket_iommu_domain_put+0x20/0xa8 [rocket]
   rocket_job_cleanup+0x20/0x254 [rocket]
   rocket_ioctl_submit+0x394/0x744 [rocket]

Signed-off-by: Johan van der Berg <johan@example.com>
---
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
index ac51bff39833..123456789abc 100644
--- a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
+++ b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
@@ -280,7 +280,8 @@ static void rocket_job_cleanup(struct kref *ref)
 						refcount);
 	unsigned int i;
 
-	rocket_iommu_domain_put(job->domain);
+	if (job->domain)
+		rocket_iommu_domain_put(job->domain);
 
 	dma_fence_put(job->done_fence);
 	dma_fence_put(job->inference_done_fence);
-- 
